
Package: distributed-regional-check-agent
Version: 1.0.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: CheckCle Team <support@checkcle.com>
Description: Distributed Regional Check Agent for CheckCle Monitoring
 A distributed regional monitoring agent that performs network checks (HTTP, DNS, 
 TCP, PING) and reports results to a central PocketBase instance. This agent can
 be deployed across different regions to provide comprehensive monitoring coverage.
 .
 Key features:
 - HTTP/HTTPS monitoring with detailed response analysis
 - DNS resolution testing with multiple record types
 - TCP connection testing with port accessibility checks
 - ICMP ping testing with packet loss and latency metrics
 - Regional service assignment and filtering
 - Real-time data reporting to PocketBase
 - Automatic service discovery and monitoring
 - Health check endpoints for agent monitoring
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.17), ca-certificates
Homepage: https://github.com/checkcle/distributed-regional-monitoring
